    1. View all applications
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a streamlined way to view applications, their status and all related data.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Select -> "Home" -> "Officer Dashboard" -> "View User Applications"</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
    2. Sort applications by the creation date
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with an easy way to view the newest or oldest applications easily.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the User Applications page (see 1.). 
    Then, select the dropdown menu above the table to the right. 
    Select whether you want to see newer applications first ('Newest to oldest' option) or older applications first ('Oldest to newest').
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
    3. Filter applications by status, applicant height, and/or date created.
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with an easy way to view applications based on common parameters.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the User Applications page (see 1.). 
    Then, select 'Show Filters'. The filter options will then appear underneath. <br />
    - To filter by status, select the checkbox for each application with the specified status that you would like to see. <br />
    - To filter by the child height, enter a minimum and/or maximum height in inches, and only applicants within those ranges will be shown. <br />
    - To filter by the date created, enter a start and/or end date, and only applications created within that range will be shown. <br />
    After you have select any combination of the above options, select 'Apply Filters.' The page will then be reloaded according to your specifications.
    You may also select 'Clear Filters' after you have applied them to see all user applications once again. <br />
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
    4. Change the status of an applicant
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a simple way to accept, reject, and waitlist applications.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the User Applications page (see 1.). Then, select "Change Status" next to an application. <br />
      - To accept an applicant, select the checkbox for "Accept User?" and then click "Update Application". <br/>
      - To waitlist an applicant, select the checkbox for "Waitlist User?", then click "Update Application". <br />
      - To reject an applicant, unselect/leave both boxes unselected and click "Update Application". <br />
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
    6. Create an application
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a way to create applications on behalf of an applicant.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the User Applications page (see 1.). Then, select "New Application" underneath the table of user applications. You will be taken to a new page with a form for user applications.
    Once you have entered at least all required details, select 'Submit Application' at the end of the form to create the application.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
