  11. Manage Cars
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a way to Create, View, Edit, and Delete cars</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the Dashboard. Then, select 'Inventory' then 'View Cars'. From here you can view all cars, choose to show a specific car, create a car, or edit/delete an existing car</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
  12. Manage Car Types
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a way to Create, View, Edit, and Delete Car Types. These serve as templates for alike cars.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the Dashboard. Then, select 'Inventory' then 'View Car Types'. From here you can view all car types, choose to show a specific car type, create a car type, or edit/delete an existing car type</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
  13. Manage Car Parts
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a way to View, Edit, and Delete Car Parts. These serve to keep track of different materials that are needed during build day for a specific car.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the Dashboard. Then, select 'Inventory' then 'View Parts'. From here you can view all car parts, choose to show a specific car part, or edit/delete an existing car part</p>
    <p><strong>Manage parts for a specific car:</strong> Navigate to the Dashboard. Then, select 'Inventory' then 'View Cars'. From here you can view all cars. Choose on 'Show' a specific car you want to manage parts for. You will see a table of all parts assigned to the car with actions for each part such as Edit/Show/Delete for each part</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 10px; user-select: none;">
  <span onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display = this.nextElementSibling.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';" style="cursor: pointer; color: #007bff; padding: 1px 0; display: inline-block; margin-top: 10px;">
  14. Creating Car Parts
  </span>
  <div style="display: none; padding: 10px; margin-top: 5px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background-color: #f9f9f9;">
    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this feature is to provide GoBabyGo Officers with a way to Create Car Parts. This method will also assign it to the desired car.</p>
    <p><strong>How to Achieve It:</strong> Navigate to the Dashboard. Then, select 'Inventory' then 'View Cars'. From here you can view all cars. Choose to 'Show' a specific car that you want to add a part to. Click on 'Edit'. Here you will see information that you can edit for the car, as well as a form for adding car parts. Once you have filled out the form click on 'Create'.</p>
  </div>
